---
import QualMethodLayout from '../../../../components/QualMethodLayout.astro';
import { interviewRigour } from '../../../../data/qual-interview-rigour';

const interviewProbes = [
  { type: 'Silent', description: 'Nod slowly; tilt head' },
  { type: 'Echo', description: 'Repeat the last sentence statement and ask respondent to continue' },
  { type: 'Neutral', description: 'Encouraging "I see" or "uh-huh"' },
  { type: 'Direct', description: 'Tell me more' },
  { type: 'Phased assertion', description: 'Imply you already know something or encourage respondent to speak' },
  { type: 'Detail', description: 'Who, where, what, when, how' },
  { type: 'Clarifying', description: 'You said "x", please describe what you meant by that' },
];

const veganQuotes = [
  { id: 'A', text: 'I always thought about the animals. They suffer a lot when we actually eat meat.' },
  { id: 'B', text: 'Why should some animal die for us? We can very well live without meat.' },
  { id: 'C', text: 'I think we have to act consciously. We cannot just think about ourselves.' },
  { id: 'D', text: 'It seems to be a health trend.' },
  { id: 'E', text: 'It just suits my lifestyle. And I want to turn really old.' },
  { id: 'F', text: 'Everyone is doing it right now. So why not trying it out! It is like a hipster thing.' },
  { id: 'G', text: 'Eating this much meat takes resources away from developing countries!' },
];

const firstOrderCodes = [
  { code: 'Animal rights', quotes: ['A', 'B'] },
  { code: 'Other people', quotes: ['C', 'G'] },
  { code: 'Hipster trend', quotes: ['D', 'F'] },
  { code: 'Health trend', quotes: ['D', 'E'] },
];

const secondOrderCodes = [
  { theme: 'Ethical reasons', codes: ['Animal rights', 'Other people'] },
  { theme: 'Trend', codes: ['Hipster trend', 'Health trend'] },
];
---

<QualMethodLayout title="Interviews" description="Qualitative interviews — semi-structured, in-depth, probes, and rigour">
  <h1>Interviews</h1>
  <p>
    <strong>Semi structured:</strong> somewhat experts, 30 minutes. Not probing, 12 questions. You need &gt;12 × 3. ×3
    because of triangulation. Need to repeat 3 times to ensure it&rsquo;s credible.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>In depth:</strong> with experts, 60 to 90 minutes. 5 questions: allow for follow up, probing. Needs &gt;7 ×
    3, also need to repeat 3 times. Explore individual experiences and perceptions in rich detail.
  </p>

  <section class="interviews-section">
    <h2>In-depth interviewing (common method)</h2>
    <ul class="interviews-list">
      <li>Use an interview guide &ldquo;guided conversation&rdquo;</li>
      <li>
        Semi-structured format &mdash; the researcher can deviate to explore interesting points or explore a new idea
        <ul>
          <li>Keep notes</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Interactive process
        <ul>
          <li>You are allowed to change questions as long as it does not change the ethics approval</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Prepare and refine the interview protocol
        <ul>
          <li>Change &ldquo;value&rdquo; to &ldquo;benefit&rdquo;</li>
          <li>Change order of questions</li>
          <li>Add new questions based on previous interviews &mdash; <strong>ITERATIVE</strong></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="interviews-section">
    <h2>Example of an interview guide</h2>
    <p class="interviews-note">
      At the start of the study, a flow diagram of questions was constructed. After a number of interviews, it was evident
      that such an initial structure is of great value, but that it was too wide.
    </p>

    <div class="interview-guide">
      <h3 class="interview-guide-heading">Opening</h3>
      <ol class="interview-guide-steps">
        <li>Explain what the study is looking at.</li>
        <li>For the record, state your organisation and your position.</li>
        <li>Which environmental problems do you see as the biggest risk to your business?</li>
        <li>What opportunities do you see around environmental aspects?</li>
        <li>
          Do you believe companies in your industry should work together on environmental projects?
          <span class="interview-guide-prompt">Why?</span>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="interview-guide-heading">Core question</h3>
      <p class="interview-guide-core">
        Is the company you work for collaborating with competitors on environmental aspects?
      </p>

      <div class="interview-guide-branches">
        <div class="interview-guide-branch">
          <h4>If no (N)</h4>
          <ol>
            <li>Why do you believe this is?</li>
            <li>What other barriers do you see?</li>
            <li>What are the three biggest barriers in your view?</li>
            <li>
              What do you believe would be the consequences if you and your competitors do not collaborate on environmental
              issues in the future?
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="interview-guide-branch">
          <h4>If yes (Y)</h4>
          <ol>
            <li>Please provide an example of environmental collaboration?</li>
            <li>Can you explain when and how this example came about?</li>
            <li>How has this example benefited your organisation?</li>
            <li>How has the example benefited society?</li>
            <li>What did you learn from this experience, both positive and negative?</li>
            <li>Are there any other examples you can think of?</li>
            <li>Which stakeholders are exerting the most pressure for you to collaborate?</li>
            <li>Are there any competitors you prefer to collaborate with? Why?</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="interview-guide-heading">Follow-up</h3>
      <p class="interview-guide-core">
        Is your company collaborating with competitors in other respects? Please elaborate.
      </p>
      <div class="interview-guide-branches">
        <div class="interview-guide-branch">
          <h4>If yes (Y)</h4>
          <p>Please provide examples.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="interview-guide-branch">
          <h4>If no (N)</h4>
          <ol>
            <li>What role should government play in encouraging competitors to work together on environmental aspects?</li>
            <li>
              What role do other third parties play in facilitating environmental cooperation in your industry?
              <ul class="interview-guide-nested">
                <li>
                  <strong>If yes:</strong> Under which conditions? What other factors would facilitate environmental
                  competition beyond its current level? What do you believe determines the level of environmental
                  cooperation in different industries?
                </li>
                <li><strong>If no:</strong> Why not?</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interviews-section">
    <h2>Why do people go vegan?</h2>
    <p class="interviews-note">
      Example of coding interview transcripts: quotes &rarr; first-order codes &rarr; second-order themes.
    </p>
    <div class="coding-flow" role="img" aria-label="Interview analysis flow from transcripts to ethical reasons and trend themes">
      <div class="coding-stage">
        <h3 class="coding-stage-title">Interview transcripts</h3>
        <div class="coding-transcripts" aria-hidden="true">
          <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="coding-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</div>
      <div class="coding-stage">
        <h3 class="coding-stage-title">Quotes / paragraphs</h3>
        <ul class="coding-quotes">
          {veganQuotes.map((quote) => (
            <li>
              <strong>Quote {quote.id}:</strong> &ldquo;{quote.text}&rdquo;
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="coding-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</div>
      <div class="coding-stage">
        <h3 class="coding-stage-title">First-order codes</h3>
        <ul class="coding-codes">
          {firstOrderCodes.map((item) => (
            <li>
              <strong>{item.code}</strong>
              <span class="coding-links">
                ({item.quotes.map((q) => `Quote ${q}`).join(', ')})
              </span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="coding-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</div>
      <div class="coding-stage">
        <h3 class="coding-stage-title">Second-order codes</h3>
        <ul class="coding-codes">
          {secondOrderCodes.map((item) => (
            <li>
              <strong>{item.theme}</strong>
              <span class="coding-links">({item.codes.join(', ')})</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interviews-section">
    <h2>Common probes in interviews*</h2>
    <div class="qual-table-wrap">
      <table class="qual-rigour-table interviews-probes-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Probe</th>
            <th scope="col">Description / example</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {interviewProbes.map((probe) => (
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">{probe.type}</th>
              <td>{probe.description}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interviews-section">
    <h2 class="qual-table-heading">Interviews (primary, qualitative)</h2>
    <div class="qual-table-wrap">
      <table class="qual-rigour-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Rigour critical</th>
            <th scope="col">Criteria for rigour</th>
            <th scope="col">Research strategy</th>
            <th scope="col">Techniques to insure rigour</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {interviewRigour.map((row) => (
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">{row.critical}</th>
              <td>{row.criteria}</td>
              <td>
                <ul>
                  {row.strategies.map((item) => (
                    <li>{item}</li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </td>
              <td>
                <ul>
                  {row.techniques.map((item) => (
                    <li>{item}</li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="qual-source">Liamputtong and Ezzy (2009)</p>
  </section>
</QualMethodLayout>

<style>
  .interviews-section {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .interviews-section > h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem 0;
  }

  h2.qual-table-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .interviews-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .interviews-list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .interviews-note {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .interview-guide {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: rgba(113, 32, 56, 0.03);
  }

  .interview-guide-heading {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.65rem 0;
  }

  .interview-guide-heading:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .interview-guide-steps {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .interview-guide-steps li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .interview-guide-prompt {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-left: 0.35rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
  }

  .interview-guide-core {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem 0;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .interview-guide-branches {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .interview-guide-branches {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .interview-guide-branch {
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .interview-guide-branch h4 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
  }

  .interview-guide-branch ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .interview-guide-branch p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .interview-guide-nested {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .interviews-probes-table {
    min-width: 24rem;
  }

  .coding-flow {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(5rem, 0.7fr) auto minmax(10rem, 1.4fr) auto minmax(8rem, 1fr) auto minmax(7rem, 0.9fr);
    gap: 0.5rem 0.35rem;
    align-items: start;
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: #fafafa;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .coding-flow {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .coding-arrow {
      text-align: center;
      transform: rotate(90deg);
      margin: 0.25rem auto;
    }
  }

  .coding-stage {
    min-width: 0;
    padding: 0.65rem 0.75rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .coding-stage-title {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem 0;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .coding-arrow {
    align-self: center;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-maroon-muted);
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .coding-transcripts {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .coding-transcripts span {
    display: block;
    width: 2.5rem;
    height: 1.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 2px;
    background: #fff;
    position: relative;
  }

  .coding-transcripts span::before {
    content: '“';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0.1rem;
    left: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  .coding-quotes,
  .coding-codes {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  .coding-quotes li,
  .coding-codes li {
    margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
  }

  .coding-quotes li:last-child,
  .coding-codes li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .coding-links {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }
</style>
